The paper deals with theoretical investigations of incompressibility and randomness in generalized representations of graphs, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The study of network topological properties, such as vertex degree, connectivity, diameter, and rigidity, is related to computer science and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of algorithmic randomness is also related to computational complexity and theoretical computer science (cs.NE, cs.SI).
